entries.femaleVariant: Antique, junky variety. Wonder if it even works.
The customer you are trying to reach is unavailable. Please leave a message.
Who is this?
Hello? Yeah, nineteen ninety-seven here – we'd like our phone back.
Hello? Anyone there?
Uh, anyone there?
Name's V.
A friend.
Not important.
Reed? Don't have time for games.
Reed…? Listen, got no time to play games.
Call me V.
A friend.
Doe'n't matter who I am. Matters who sent me.
Daytime, note it.
Not exactly loquacious, our man of mystery…
Fossil's prolly busted.
Or you flubbed the number.
Ah, c'mon. Answer.
I'll have a double cheeseburg while you're at it.
Capitán Caliente. Guy clearly went down with this place.
The fuck do we do now?
entries.maleVariant: What the fuck do we do now?

entries.femaleVariant: Hello...?
C'mon, pick up.
Stash house, by the looks of it.
Ain't nothin' without your health! Check out Ronald's preem stims!
Get your fresh-klepped shards here!
Best prices in Dogtown! Certified resale!
Man, fuck the corps – shop local! Shop with Ronald! Ronnie! The Ronster!
Show me what you got.
I'll be damned! A real, live customer! Heh. What can I getcha?
Whaddaya need, angel?
How's biz?
Caliente closed?
Let's see whatcha got.
Preemest shit you ever seen!
'Ey yo, I love a good loiter… but you gonna buy some shit or not?
Hey, Capitán Caliente – closed?
How's biz? Eddies flowin'?
But tomorrow's another day. Peeps know Ronald's shop always got what they need!
Nah, choom, delta crash got everyone skezzin'.
Shut 'n boarded. Owner talked shit about Kurt. Mad disrespect. Had no choice – hanged hisself out back.
Know a way inside? Pay you for your trouble.
Ey, you a fresh face, so listen up – here in Dtown, ya watch whatcha say. Talk shit to the wrong choom – blam, ya dead.
Anyone inside?
Man of biz y'are, so let's cut a deal. I slip ya a few eds, you tell me how to slip inside.
Anyone inside right now?
You payin' for trouble, but OK. Don't ever bail on eddies, huh? Hah…
Could just prefer text. Damn sure I do.
The new – ahem – "owners" are drainin' power from down the road.
Don't know, don't care. Buy somethin' or get off my ass.
Check the cables on the wall – sure to connect somewhere. Tinker 'round, reset the power, betcha security trinkets just might go dark.
Sounds promising.
If you ain't a payin' customer, you a leavin' customer.
Half a Dogtown's chasin' Rosalind Myers like bitches in heat. Shit's fake news.
You blockin' my light, choom.
[Hang up]
We know she's in there! Set her free! Or we will!
WHERE IS MYERS?! WHERE IS MYERS?!
Dogtown will PAY!
Hansen, you fucking shitstain!
Move the fuck back! Now!
Give me a reason, you Washington whores!
You playin' rough? Come on, then!
Wanna eat lead, fuckers?! Huh?!
Tell me about the 'hood.
Longshore Stacks –  whaddaya know?
Look like a choom who's been around Dtown.
OK, Longshore Stacks – whaddaya know?
Like whatcha see, huh? Big fan myself. Place got a real history, y'know?
Everythin' ya see here, every lil' piece of fuckin' scrap metal 'n' shit is pre-war, choom.
Them containers – used to hold bricks 'n' beams for buildin' the 'hood. Shit got klepped, obvi, but them big-ass boxes? Ain't gone nowhere.
Now, we Dtowners, we resourceful. Some clever chooms grabbed 'em and behold – preem livin' space. In highrises, no less! Ain't no shit go to waste here, y'know?
Gotta say, first time I'm in the 'hood. Sooo, Terra – got any, uh, travel tips?
entries.maleVariant: Gotta say, first time in the 'hood. Sooo, Terra – got any… travel tips?

entries.femaleVariant: Hmph. The place was a fuckin' quant's paradise years back – talkin' space flight, chrome o' the future, all sortsa tech. Shit'd fry your skullsponge.
Now, nothin' but dirt 'n dust 'n' scavs. Rat-ass motherfuckers runnin' the place.
Ya go to Terra Cognita – you a corpse incognita… Hahah! Geddit? Incognita…
What's up with this tree?
Been wantin' to ask, Ronnie… What's up with all the pics on that tree?
Tha'ss whatcha call tradition, choom.
See any badges 'round here? Mm-mm. So your chooms go missin', yeah? Whatcha gon' do? Call Hansen? Nah, best go on you own hunt.
So you don't call no BARGHEST dogs when someone near 'n' dear go missin'. Ya pin a pic to that tree. Attach you's detes, sit tight 'n' pray fo' contact.
Peeps ever find their chooms? Well, sometimes. Maybe. Not really. Not 'bout that. 'S 'bout hope, feel me?
Hang a pic and ya feel like ya done somethin'. Better than sittin' on your ass, yeah?
Been to the stadium. Quite a sight.
Been to the Stadium. Interesting place.
Around? Sheeit, gurl, this is my home turf! Who d'ya think I am?
entries.maleVariant: Around? Sheeit, playah, this is my home turf! Who d'ya think I am?

entries.femaleVariant: Hmph! You talkin' to the "Pacifica Typhoon," choom! Ay-kay-ay "The DT Prodigy"!... Yeeeah, OK, that one ain't my fave.
When they was pumpin' me wit boosters, could blast a hundred meters in six-point-oh! Yeah, ya heard right!
Now I ain't do hardly a hundred a DAY no more. But what'm sayin' is – hell yeah, I been around!
"Pacifica Typhoon"? Seriously?
"Typhoon Ronnie," huh? You serious?
Scan the old screamers if yous a doubter! Ol' Ronnie was a LEGEND... i-in the makin'.
Hm... How'd your risin' star suddenly flop?
entries.maleVariant: Hm... How'd your, uh, risin' star suddenly flop?

entries.femaleVariant: Well… there's this chick, Fiona. Had this, uhm, center for gifted youth 'n' shit. Future sports stars. All good, right?
We talkin' a roof overhead, real food, trainin', boosters 'n' chrome. And heaps of chrome, choom.
Shit was all rainbows 'n' roses till ya stumbled. And choom, I fuckin' wiped out. Landed in the Dtown street with mean-ass migraines 'n' insomnia. An' I was lucky, too.
Since I got you…
Since I got you, was gonna ask…
Hit me, choom. Day's slower 'n' a molasses flood.
Tell me about the 'hood.
Got some questions 'bout D-town, actually…
Sure thing, toss 'em up.
Uh-huh. Had big plans to set up shop there, y'know? But wooo, the competition whooped my typhoon ass.
Y'know, Nighthawks was roostin' there while Hansen was still shittin' his diapers. How's it go…? Good times make bad chooms, then bad chooms fuck shit up?
Bottom line – 's all 'bout the eddies. Who got the most scratch? Hansen! Stadium ain't his main biz, oh no. But I ain't gonna say no more on that, hah!
Dtown districts – tell me what you know.
Some points of interest caught my eye…
Dtown's districts – whaddaya know?
Golden Pacific sounds grandiose.
Luxor Heights – what's the story?
Since we're already talkin'…
Came through an expo hall recently.
There's this skyscraper…
Got a pyramid here, right?
Hah! Which ones, baby girl?
Got some pretty unique places 'round here...
This 'hood just exudin' clever, now, ain't it? Hahah!
Luxor Heights – know anything about 'em?
Golden Pacific. Grandiose name, am I right?
Ey, best not snoop 'round there. Them Voodoo Boys been doin' voodoo shit since they made it their crib.
Sheeit, choom, suits promised eddies rainin' down from every window, peeps shittin' solid gold!
Yeah, yeah, w-whacha thinkin'?
Came through this kinda… expo hall? Some curious mockups of all kinds of buildings there.
Even got a pyramid. Hard to miss, that one.
Big skyscraper – know anything about it?
Ho-ho! You got guts, girl! Liked whatcha saw? Them suits musta been trippin BALLS comin' up with them district plans, hahaha!
entries.maleVariant: Ho-ho! You got guts, man! Liked whatcha saw? Them suits musta been trippin BALLS comin' up with them district plans, hahaha!

entries.femaleVariant: Pretty preem, hmm? Fixers think so fo' sure. Biz talks get drowned out by wild party hubbub and tracks that're fire. Privacy guaranteed, hmm?
Suits called it the Black Sapphire way back when. Folks call it the "hotel" or "tower" these days. Place's gilded, I hear. Pretty much outta reach for us mortals.
Thanks, real helpful. Seem to really know your way around.
Fuck it, why not?
Nah, pass.
Know what? Fuck it, why not. Be nice to know what the street's sayin'.
Eh, thanks, think I got it from here. Later, Ronnie.
entries.maleVariant: Thanks, think I got it from here. Later, Ronnie.

entries.femaleVariant: Well, shit! In my line o' work, it's all about the gossip. The juicier, the better. Could send some real spicy ones your way, if you's so inclined!
Yeeeah, startin' to get me now, hah! Gotta get a leg up whatevah way you can in good old Dtown! Stay in touch, choom.
OK, OK… Well, good luck to ya, sister.
entries.maleVariant: Okay, okay… Well, good luck to ya, bruh.

entries.femaleVariant: Now, they hop 'tween two beds – scavs' 'n' Hansen's. 'Fore ya visit, it's good to know who they be fuckin' 'round with at the time. Askin' for trouble otherwise.
Proved true 'nuff fo' my man Hansen. He the only one makin' fat stacks in that place, huh.
Expo ain't no place for civvies. Ya got pre-war goods 'n' shit there… Best stay clear, 'specially since peeps been hearin' blasts 'n explosions. No thank you.
Heheh! Then WHAM! Reality kicked in. Gonks prolly woke up face-down in the streets, thinkin' "where'd it all go wrong?!"
Bangin' tunes, dense lines o' snow-white, and the biz is IN, choom! Tha'ss how ya get in them major leagues!
Bottom's open to all the riff-raff. Upper levels, though? Shit's for VIPs. Big playas, big biz, feel me? Maybe gonna visit myself, hahahahahaaa!
Apple o' Hansen's eye, his golden egg. He wanna make chooms witchu, he gon' invite you there.
Hear the view from the top's mothafuckin' nova. Might be a lil' crazy, but... I ain't cray-cray enough to find out fo' myself.
Golden Pacific's a BARGHEST breedin' ground. Got their biz, logistics, fun times – all in one helluva dangerous place if you's not one of them dawgs.
Andrew Jackson. Basketball court.
Why avoid Terra Cognita? Any tips?
As I says, steer the fuck clear o' Terra Cognita.
Golden Pacific be in the north of Dtown. Got this hill there, Luxor Heights. Name makes a promise and delivers – preem views, ten outta ten.
Longshore Stacks is the west side. Place got history, feel me? South is Terra Cognita – ya best stay the fuck clear o' there.
Mmm, everythin' there's pre-Unity-War-shit, get me…? Start seein' containers, means ya found the place.
Now, we Dtowners, we resourceful. Some clever chooms grabbed 'em and behold – preem livin' space. In highrises, no less! Ain't no shit go to waste here, y'know?
Huh...
U-S-A! U-S-A!
Terrorists!
Powerful and united!
Damn you all!
